snippet.textDisplay: Shilpa Rao - what a gorgeous voice! The bit with the sagar veena is just incredible. Not sure I cared for the segue into Ali Noor's rock vocals at the end - it overpowered the low-pitched richness of Shilpa's tones. Personally I would've preferred this song as a duet between Shilpa and Ali Hamza. But it is definitely one of the best songs of this season.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm writing this after having listened to the song for a gazillion times as getting goosebumps ev single time.  To me, its a greater win for Punjab and I'll explain how. Sohni Mahiwal signify the richness in Punjab culture. The song is in Punjabi, a boli which knows no borders. Its a collaboration between ppl of Punjab (Noori & Rao) above borders. Above all is river Chenab, the purity of Punjab itself. Blended in a beautifully orchestrated music and lyrics to make it even more magical. A win, not for Coke Studio alone,  but for Punjab.

Another aspect is of spirituality. Sohni signifies self. Mahiwal as the divine Lord. River as the difficulties prevailing. Gharra as the way to reach Lord (which isn't the appropriate one,  and Gharra irself says that I'm kacha). The final verses of Pharr palrra pakkay ........ is the crux where its must that you follow the lead of a sound guide to reach Lord. This is all what i get of it. Comments welcome.
